tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ClientInformation (
    client_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    client_name VARCHAR(255),
    client_age INT,
    client_gender VARCHAR(10),
    client_email VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE clients (
  client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  client_name VARCHAR(255),
  client_age INT,
  client_gender VARCHAR(10),
  client_address VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE services (
  service_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  service_name VARCHAR(255),
  service_date DATE,
  service_provider VARCHAR(255),
  client_id INT REFERENCES clients(client_id)
)

CREATE TABLE client_services (
  client_id UUID,
  service_id UUID,
  service_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES clients(client_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (service_id) REFERENCES services(service_id)
);
CREATE TABLE clients (client_id INT PRIMARY KEY, client_name VARCHAR(50), client_email VARCHAR(100), client_phone VARCHAR(15), client_address VARCHAR(200))
CREATE TABLE services (service_id INT PRIMARY KEY, service_name VARCHAR(50), service_description VARCHAR(200))
CREATE TABLE client_services (client_id INT, service_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES clients(client_id), FOREIGN KEY (service_id) REFERENCES services(service_id))

CREATE TABLE program_evaluation (evaluation_id INT PRIMARY KEY, client_id INT, service_id INT, evaluation_date DATE, evaluation_rating INT, FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES clients(client_id), FOREIGN KEY (service_id) REFERENCES services(service_id))

CREATE TABLE client_services (
    client_id INT,
    service_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (client_id, service_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES clients(client_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (service_id) REFERENCES services(service_id)
);

CREATE TABLE program_evaluation (
    evaluation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    service_id INT,
    rating INT,
    comments TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES clients(client_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (service_id) REFERENCES services(service_id)
);
